<td colspan="3" style="background:#bebebe; color:#000000;"><small><b>Notes and references</b></small></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="3" style="text-align:left;"><small>1. Prior to the passage of the <a href="/wiki/Twelfth_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution" title="Twelfth Amendment to the United States Constitution">Twelfth Amendment</a> in 1804, each Presidential elector would cast two ballots; the highest vote-getter would become President and the runner-up would become Vice President. Thus, in 1796, the <a href="/wiki/Democratic-Republican_Party" title="Democratic-Republican Party">Democratic-Republican Party</a> fielded Jefferson as a Presidential candidate, but he came in second and therefore became Vice President.</small></td>
</tr>
